CloudFront + Advance shield
------------------------------
Step 6

[ SHIELD ADVANCED — SETUP STEPS ]

  Step 1 — Open Shield Console
    AWS Console → search "Shield" → AWS Shield

  Step 2 — Subscribe
    Shield Console → Getting Started
    → Subscribe to Shield Advanced
    NOTE: $3,000/month, 12-month commitment
    NEED: Business or Enterprise Support plan

  Step 3 — Add Protected Resources
    Shield Console → Protected Resources → Add Resources
    Resources to add:
      [ ] CloudFront distribution      -- Select your CloudFront distribution (Attach Shield Advanced to CloudFront ✅)
      [ ] Route 53 hosted zone
      [ ] ALB / NLB
      [ ] Elastic IP (EC2)
      [ ] Global Accelerator

  Step 4 — Associate WAF Web ACL (for Layer 7)     -- Link WAF to Shield Advanced ✅  -- both same as Step 5 just different path to create
    Shield Console → Protected Resources
    → Select resource → Associate WAF Web ACL
    NOTE: Create WAF Web ACL first if you don't have one
          AWS WAF → Create Web ACL → then come back here

  Step 5 — Health-based Detection (recommended)
    Shield Console → Protected Resources
    → Select resource → Associate Health Check
    NOTE: Create Route 53 health check first

  Step 6 — Enable DRT Proactive Engagement
    Shield Console → Overview
    → Edit Proactive Engagement → Enable
    Add emergency contact: email + phone
    NOTE: Requires Business or Enterprise Support

  Step 7 — Monitor
    Shield Console → Events
    → View by resource or time range
